-- South Korea Household Income Rises for 11th Straight Quarter
-- B y   C y n t h i a   K i m
-- 2012-08-17T03:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-17/south-korea-household-income-rises-for-11th-straight-quarter.html
South Korean household income rose
for an 11th straight quarter from a year earlier even as
economic growth cooled amid  Europe ’s debt crisis.  Average monthly income at households increased 6.2 percent
to 3.9 million won ($3,441) in the second quarter from a year
earlier after a 6.9 percent gain in the previous three months,
Statistics Korea said in a report today.  Household’s monthly spending excluding tax and social
security-related payments increased 3.6 percent to 2.4 million
won last quarter from a year earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cynthia Kim in Seoul at 
